  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 0f3a2c8c7b8f4d9c9d5a3d11d5f50101, type: 3}
  m_Name: PokedexBlueJay
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  entryId: bird_bluejay
  commonName: Blue Jay
  scientificName: Cyanocitta cristata
  icon: {fileID: 2800000, guid: f6d44515531016540a2eca4aad3dd89d, type: 3}
  category: Bird
  habitat: Oak & Mixed Forests
  height: 22 - 30 cm
  weight: 70 - 100 g
  diet: Omnivore
  rarity: Common
  shortDescription: A highly intelligent, loud corvid sporting striking blue, white,
    and black plumage with a prominent crest.
  behaviorNotes: Curious and highly active in branches. Moves in small, dynamic family
    groups and can lower or raise its feather crest.
  observationTips: Easy to find by listening for their loud, raucous calls. They
    prefer hanging around oak and nut-bearing trees.
  funFact: Blue Jays are excellent mimics. They frequently imitate the calls of hawks
    to scare other birds away from feeding areas.
  facts:
  - The brilliant blue color of their feathers is an optical illusion caused by light
    scattering off cells, not actual blue pigment.
  - They play a crucial role in forest growth by burying thousands of acorns each
    autumn, many of which sprout into oak trees.
  - Blue jays communicate with a vast vocabulary of clicks, whistles, and structural
    crest adjustments to signal intent to their flock.
